details.content: Tension prevailed at the airport as protesters announced that social activist Trupti Desai and her six colleagues, who reached here at around 4.40 am from Pune, would not be allowed to go out of the airport.

details.title: Protesters lay siege to Kochi Airport
details.content:
Kerala: Protesters gather outside Cochin International Airport. Trupti Desai, the founder of Bhumata Brigade, has arrived at the airport from Pune. Security has been heightened. She had written to Kerala CM seeking security for her visit to #SabrimalaTemple on 17 November. pic.twitter.com/7FwknubhFn

— ANI (@ANI) November 15, 2018
Desai had written to Kerala CM Pinarayi Vijayan seeking security for her visit to Sabrimala Temple on 17 November.

Won't allow Trupti Desai to go out from airport using police vehicle or other govt means.Airport taxies also won't take her.If she wants,she can use her own vehicle.There will be agitations all along her way even if she goes out from airport: MN Gopi, BJP, outside Cochin airport pic.twitter.com/sRoT0kZtUj

— ANI (@ANI) November 16, 2018

Speaking to ANI, the social activist said, "protestors should not resort to violence. Once we reach there, we'll see what level of security state gives us. Even if the state doesn't give us any security, we'll still go, but I can be attacked. I have received so many threats of attack & killing."
An all-party meeting Thursday failed to end the deadlock over the Supreme Court verdict that lifted the ban on entry for women of menstrual age to Sabarimala temple.
Section 144 has been imposed in Nilakkal, Pamba and Sannidhanam as the Ayyappa shrine will open today.

Kochi: Trupti Desai, founder of Bhumata Brigade, at Cochin International Airport. Protests are underway outside the airport against her visit to #SabarimalaTemple. #Kerala pic.twitter.com/T3y1JEj8ZH

— ANI (@ANI) November 16, 2018

Opposition leader Ramesh Chennithala on Thursday lashed out at Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan for the adamant stance on the Sabarimala issue and said the government has the responsibility to protect the interests of the believers. He said both the CPM and the BJP are playing a dangerous game by dividing the society on communal basis.
Protesters reach the arrival gate of the Kochi airport, likely to affect the regural functioning, reports Malayala Manorama.
Discussion for providing security cover for Trupti Desai is still underway. It will depend on the situation. : Kerala police chief Loknath Behera
Unlike the security cover during the Thulam month pooja and hithira Atta Vishesham, the police deployment will be higher as the government expects a heavy rush from Friday.
Ready to cooperate with Kerala police: Trupti Desai to local media

Kochi: Trupti Desai, founder of Bhumata Brigade, having breakfast at Cochin International Airport as she hasn't been able to leave the airport yet due to protests being carried out against her visit to #Sabarimala Temple. #Kerala pic.twitter.com/ILDV7silTx

— ANI (@ANI) November 16, 2018
Ready to cooperate with Kerala police: Trupti Desai to local media

#sabarimalastandoff ; Kerala High Court on Friday granted bail to six accused persons in a case registered in connection with violence erupted in Nilakkal during a protest against women entry in #SabarimalaTemple @BJP4India @CMOKerala

— P Ramdas (@PRamdas_TNIE) November 16, 2018

Meanwhile, the Kerala HC on Friday dismissed anticipatory bail plea of activist Rehana Fathima,who had tried to enter Sabarimala, but was blocked by protesters, an accused in a case registered by Pathanamthitta police alleging hurting religious sentiments (295A IPC).
Protests against Trupti Desai in different Kottayam temples, reports Malayala Manorama.

Translation from Marathi:

We arrived at the Kochi Airport at 4.30 am. We are being opposed by hundreds of protesters. The Kerala government has provided us adequate security with 150 police personnel. Despite this, the police are unable to handle the situation. The protesters are saying that the vehicle I take outside the airport will be attacked. - Trupti Desai on Facebook

We tried to book a taxi two to three times, but the drivers have been threatened that their vehicle will be vandalised if they offer us a drive. Police have said that we can't go outside now: Trupti Desai to ANI

Police tried to evacuate us from another gate but protesters were there as well. Does this mean protesters are scared that we'll reach Sabarimala once we reach Nilakkal, or, are they trying to scare us? We won't return until we have 'darshan' - Trupti Desai to ANI.
Senior advocate Aryamma Sundaram will appear for the Nair Service Society (NSS) at the Supreme Court in the absence of K Parashan who is in Chennai at the moment, according to Malyala Manorama.

details.title: Send back Trupti Desai: Rahul Easwar requests Kerala Police
details.content:
Would like to humbly & formally request @TheKeralaPolice to try to send back Trupti Desai & her feminist group back from airport itself.

Protests are gathering momentum on the roads from Kochi to kottayam and then on way to Holy #Sabarimala

We will fully cooperate with police

— Rahul Easwar (@RahulEaswar) November 16, 2018

details.title: Devaswom Minister breaks silence
details.content: Kerala Devaswom Minister Kadakampally Surendran asked to ''wait for some time and not to give pressure'' on Bhumatha Brigade Founder and Activist Trupti Desai visit to Sabarimala, violating all century old traditions following the Supreme Court order, reported UNI.

details.title: Police personnel deployed in four phases
details.content: Kerala Police beefs up security. Deploys 15,259 police personnel in four phases during the festive season, reports TNIE correspondent Dileep V Kumar.

#Kerala Police to deploy a platoon of Thunderbolt in addition to a 40 member police commando team with 20 members each at #Sannidhanam and #Pampa respectively #Sabarimala @BJP4Keralam @INCKerala @NewIndianXpress

— Dileep V Kumar (@dileepvk_TNIE) November 16, 2018
Newly elected priests to take charge at Sannidhanam and Malikappuram as Sanctum sanctorum of Sabarimala temple to open at 5 pm. (ENS)

details.title: Cochin airport authorities say they are reviewing situation
details.content: The Cochin International Airport authorities said it is a high security zone and no protest should be held on the airport premises. The protests have caused inconveniences to passengers but the authorities have not initiated any steps to remove them considering the volatile situation. Read detailed report here

details.title: Trupti Desai faces massive protests at Cochin International Airport
Kerala govt requests Trupti Desai to return
details.content: Kerala government officials have started negotiations with activist Trupti Desai, reported Mathrubhubhumi.com. They have requested Trupti to return in view of the on-going protests by devotees, the website added.

details.title: Under present situations, it is not possible to escort Trupti Desai outside airport: Kerala police
details.content: Following their discussions with CIAL MD and CISF, police officials said under the present situations, it is not possible to take Trupti Desai outside the airport, reported Manoramaonline. Meanwhile, airport officials shared that protests by Ayyappa devotees have affected the operations of CIAL, added the website.

details.title: Kochi IG issues strict dress code for cops on duty at Sabarimala shrine
details.content: In view of the volatile situation at Sabarimala shrine, police officers have been told to follow strict dress code while on duty at the temple. The cops stationed at Nadapandal have been instructed to carry lathis and stone shields with them, reported The News Minute.com. According to orders issued by Kochi range IG Vijay Sakahre, exceptions have been given only to those officers stationed at the 18 steps and the sopanam, added the website.

details.content:

details.title: Emergency meeting of Devaswom Board begins at Pamba
details.content: Officials of Devaswom Board are currently attending an emergency meeting at Pamba to discuss submitting a review petition against the Supreme Court's verdict allowing women of all ages into Sabarimala, reported Manoramaonline.com.

details.title: Will provide only security to Trupti Desai, she must find her own mode of transportation, accommodation: Kerala police
details.content: Kerala cops have offered security to activist, Trupti Desai, reported Manoramaonline.com. However, she must find her own mode of transportation and accommodation, added the website quoting a senior police official.

details.title: Sabarimala protests: Kerala HC grants bail to six accused
details.content: Kerala High Court on Friday granted bail to six accused persons, who were arrested in connection with the violence in Sabarimala and Nilakkal. Read full story here

details.title: Sabarimala shrine opens for Mandala Pooja-Makaravilakku season
details.content:
#Kerala: #SabarimalaTemple opens for 62-day long Mandala Pooja-Magaravilaku annual pilgrimage season. pic.twitter.com/hTqqmVdzDg

— ANI (@ANI) November 16, 2018

details.title: 200 booked at Cochin airport
details.content: Police have registered a suo motu case against 200 people who staged protest at the Cochin airport to block exit of social activist Trupti Desai.
